║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 8.3: Buffer Navigation                ║
║  Category: Goto Mode             Difficulty: ★★★ Advanced       ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  g n     Go to next buffer (open file)
  g p     Go to previous buffer
  g a     Go to last accessed file (alternate file)
  g m     Go to last modified file
  H       Previous buffer (Zed shortcut, not standard Helix)
  L       Next buffer (Zed shortcut, not standard Helix)

NOTE: H and L are Zed-specific additions for quick buffer switching.

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  Buffer navigation commands work across open files in Zed.
  This exercise teaches the concepts — practice them in your
  real workflow.

  For now: edit this file to fill in the command for each scenario.

